---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation" description="How to install and set up Marrow UI in your project" activeSection="installation">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Installation</h1>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">Get Marrow UI running in your project in under 5 minutes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mw-separator"></div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Prerequisites</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Marrow UI requires two dependencies:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> &mdash; for utility-class styling</li>
            <li><strong>Alpine.js</strong> &mdash; for interactive components (dropdowns, modals, tabs, etc.)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Both can be included via CDN or installed via npm.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Quick Start (CDN)</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">The fastest way to get started. Add these to your HTML <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">&lt;head&gt;</code>:</p>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn" title="Copy to clipboard">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
            </button>
            <pre><code>&lt;!-- Tailwind CSS (CDN) --&gt;
&lt;script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- Alpine.js --&gt;
&lt;script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/alpinejs@3.x.x/dist/cdn.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- Marrow UI Theme CSS --&gt;
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/marrow-theme.css"&gt;
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/marrow.css"&gt;

&lt;!-- Marrow UI Alpine Components --&gt;
&lt;script src="/js/marrow.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Project Setup</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">For a full project setup with the build system and config file:</p>

          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-6">1. Clone the repository</h3>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn" title="Copy to clipboard">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
            </button>
            <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/marrow-ui/marrow-ui.git
cd marrow-ui</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-6">2. Customize your config</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Edit <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">marrow.config.js</code> to set your theme colors, compactness, radius, fonts, and more. Every option is documented with comments.</p>

          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-6">3. Build the theme</h3>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn" title="Copy to clipboard">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
            </button>
            <pre><code>node build.js</code></pre>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">This generates <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">dist/css/marrow-theme.css</code> from your config. Include this file along with <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">marrow.css</code> in your project.</p>

          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-6">4. Preview</h3>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn" title="Copy to clipboard">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
            </button>
            <pre><code>npx serve dist</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">File Structure</h2>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <pre><code>your-project/
├── marrow.config.js    # Theme configuration
├── css/
│   ├── marrow-theme.css  # Generated theme (CSS custom properties)
│   └── marrow.css        # Component base styles
├── js/
│   └── marrow.js         # Alpine.js component definitions
└── your-pages/
    └── ...               # Your HTML files using Marrow components</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Using with Tailwind Config</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If you're using Tailwind CSS with a build step (not CDN), extend your <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">tailwind.config.js</code> to use Marrow's CSS custom properties:</p>
          <div class="mw-code-block">
            <button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn" title="Copy to clipboard">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
            </button>
            <pre><code>// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: 'hsl(var(--marrow-primary) / &lt;alpha-value&gt;)',
        secondary: 'hsl(var(--marrow-secondary) / &lt;alpha-value&gt;)',
        accent: 'hsl(var(--marrow-accent) / &lt;alpha-value&gt;)',
        destructive: 'hsl(var(--marrow-destructive) / &lt;alpha-value&gt;)',
        muted: 'hsl(var(--marrow-muted) / &lt;alpha-value&gt;)',
        // ... add all colors you need
      },
    },
  },
};</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mw-alert">
          <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-1">Next Steps</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Read the <a href="/docs/customization/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Customization guide</a> to learn how to configure your theme, or browse the <a href="/docs/components/button/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Components</a> to start building.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

</DocsLayout>
